  <number>		display message <number>
  <return>		display current message
  next			display next message
  prev			display previous message
  delete <msgs>		mark messages for deletion
  undelete <msgs>	remove mark on messages
  move <msgs> <mailboxes>  copies messages into <mailboxes> and "deletes"
  scan <msgs> [all]	scan specified messages in current mailbox
  header <msgs> [all]	print summary of specified messages in current mailbox
  gsearch <expr>	searches all mailboxes for <expr>
  change <mailbox>	change current mailbox to <mailbox>
  list			lists all mailboxes
  boxname		displays name of current mailbox
  reply <msg>		reply to the specified message or current message
  Reply <msg>		reply to message, send reply to all recipients
  editforward <msg>	send a new message with current specified included
  forward <msg>		forward the specified message after editing new message
  output <msgs> <file>	appends message onto specified file
  quit			leave READMAIL (asks if should make deletions)
  ! <command>		escape to shell
  > <file>		write message to file
  | <command(s)>	pipe message to command

   <msgs> may be a number (3), range (5-8), logical expression on words in
    header fields (FROM:schatz), or omitted (current message assumed).
    e.g.  delete 3,5-8     or    scan FROM:schatz&SUBJECT:readmail
